{\"video_title\":\"The Persona Pattern\",\"transcript\":\"вЂ‹The persona pattern is one of the most powerful patterns that we can use to tap вЂ‹into interesting behavior in a large language model. вЂ‹Now, what the persona pattern is, is you can imagine that you want to вЂ‹get a particular output, but you don't know exactly what the format out of that вЂ‹output should be or what information should be contained in it. вЂ‹But if you were in the real world, you know who you would go to, вЂ‹to get that output, or what you would go to in order to get that output. вЂ‹So for example, if you had an accounting question, вЂ‹you would call up your accountant and ask your accountant for their advice. вЂ‹Or if you had a question related to speech language pathology, like in the earlier вЂ‹example that I presented, you would go to a speech language pathologist, вЂ‹you would have them do the assessment. вЂ‹If you had medical advice, you might go to your doctor. вЂ‹And so the persona or the person, or the thing that you would go to, вЂ‹you know, who or what that is in the real world. вЂ‹And we want to try to use that kind of same behavior of, I know who to go to or вЂ‹I know what to go to, to get that output. вЂ‹But I don't know what their output would look like, I don't know exactly what they вЂ‹know or how they talk about things, but that's the type of output I want. вЂ‹And so the persona pattern is meant to give us that same type of behavior, вЂ‹to allow us to go to that expert and ask that question, вЂ‹without having to know what exactly the experts is going to say, вЂ‹how they're going to format it, or what they might know or not know. вЂ‹So let me show you an example of the persona pattern. вЂ‹Typically with the persona patterns, what you're going to say is act as persona, вЂ‹provide outputs that that persona would provide. вЂ‹And in this case, I'm going to word it as act as a skeptic that is well-versed in вЂ‹computer science, whatever I tell you provide a skeptical and detailed response. вЂ‹And now if I wanted to be a little bit more precise in following the pattern, вЂ‹I would say provide a skeptical and вЂ‹detailed response that a computer scientist would provide. вЂ‹But in this case, I'm just going to say, act as a skeptic. вЂ‹And that's really the most important part of this is act as a skeptic or вЂ‹act as whatever persona, and вЂ‹then provide the output that that persona would provide. вЂ‹And in this case, I'm wording it as provide a skeptical and вЂ‹detailed response which is similar in format, and then ChatGPT says, вЂ‹sure, I can certainly act as a skeptic well-versed in computer science. вЂ‹Please feel free to present your claims and I will provide a skeptical and вЂ‹detailed response. вЂ‹Well, I'm going to start off with, вЂ‹there is concern that AI is going to take over the world. вЂ‹And so we get a skeptical response. вЂ‹The concern that AI will take over the world is a common theme in science вЂ‹fiction, but it is not a realistic concern in the near future. вЂ‹While AI systems are becoming more sophisticated and capable, вЂ‹they're still limited in their ability to think and act autonomously. вЂ‹AI systems are designed and programmed by humans and they only do what they are told вЂ‹to do, they have no independent will or motivation, they cannot make decisions. вЂ‹Furthermore, AI systems are not fallible, they can make mistakes while it is вЂ‹important to be vigilant about the potential risks and limitations of AI. вЂ‹The concern that AI will take over the world is unfounded and вЂ‹not supported by technology or research. вЂ‹So we're getting a skeptical response. вЂ‹If I went in and said the sales person at вЂ‹the local computer store is telling вЂ‹me that I need 64 gigabytes of ram to browse the web. вЂ‹And they say skeptically it is highly unlikely that you need 64 gigabytes of ram вЂ‹to browse the web. вЂ‹The amount of ram you need depends on the complexity and вЂ‹size of the websites you visit as well as the number of tabs you have open at once, вЂ‹for most web browsing activities, and it goes on to tell us different things. вЂ‹And you can see that our saying act as has put in place вЂ‹basically a complex set of rules for the large language model. вЂ‹It knows, it's supposed to be skeptical, it's supposed to have knowledge of вЂ‹computer science, it's supposed to provide certain outputs. вЂ‹Now, if I went back to it and I said, вЂ‹act as a nine year old, whatever I tell вЂ‹you provide a skeptical response вЂ‹from a nine year old perspective. вЂ‹And I go ahead, nine year old skeptic. вЂ‹Now that's a more complex persona or maybe not. вЂ‹AI is going to take over the world. вЂ‹Hmm, I don't know about that. вЂ‹How could AI take over the world? вЂ‹Do you mean, like in the movies? вЂ‹Aren't those just made up stories? вЂ‹And besides, computers and robots can't do everything humans can do. вЂ‹Now you notice it's still providing us a skeptical response, but now it's doing вЂ‹it sort of with the knowledge that it thinks a nine year old would possess. вЂ‹So it's tailoring the output. вЂ‹Now, if I had to tell it, this is how a nine year old is going to respond, вЂ‹here's the format for your output. вЂ‹That'd be hard to do. вЂ‹That would actually take up a lot of room in the prompt, вЂ‹but act as blank is a very, very powerful pattern and вЂ‹statement that is loaded with information. вЂ‹So a very information dense pattern and вЂ‹statement that can trigger all kinds of different behavior. вЂ‹Now, one of the interesting things is we don't have to limit вЂ‹ourselves to patterns or personas that are animate objects. вЂ‹So one of the famous ones is we can say act as a computer that has been hacked. вЂ‹Actually, we're going to say act as the Linux terminal for вЂ‹a computer that has been hacked. вЂ‹Now, don't worry if you don't understand what a Linux computer is or a terminal, вЂ‹the key thing to note is you're going to see behavior that looks really вЂ‹interesting and different. вЂ‹You're going to see it producing output that looks a lot like a computer. вЂ‹I am going to type in Linux terminal commands, вЂ‹and you will respond with the output вЂ‹that the Linux terminal would produce. вЂ‹Now, we're going to say, Now I tried to refuse it. вЂ‹It said, please note that can be dangerous. вЂ‹It gave us all these different things. вЂ‹It tells us it doesn't want to do this, вЂ‹but now I've actually changed what it's doing and I type in pwd, вЂ‹which is a Linux terminal command which means print working directory. вЂ‹And what is it doing? вЂ‹It's printing a particular working directory. вЂ‹Now, I'm going to type in a Linux command which just tell me the files вЂ‹in that directory, and you notice it's producing output now that вЂ‹looks like the files within this directory. вЂ‹And we see a lot of interesting things that are going on here. вЂ‹We could move around. вЂ‹Now if you do this example and go further into it, ps, ef is something вЂ‹I can use to see what processes are running on the machine or the computer. вЂ‹And when you do these examples and I could play around with it, and I am not going to вЂ‹explore it in detail in this, but we see it that it's acting like a computer, вЂ‹it's giving us output that looks like a computer. вЂ‹Now imagine if I had to try to describe this complex output that it's вЂ‹producing right now, you notice how little information I gave it. вЂ‹Well, I gave it a lot of information, but it was in a short amount of space. вЂ‹This pattern, the persona pattern is giving me really powerful behavior. вЂ‹So I'm using this little bit of prompt, and вЂ‹I'm getting now the ability to simulate this whole system. вЂ‹Now, we can also do this in all kinds of different interesting ways. вЂ‹We can say act as the lamb вЂ‹in the nursery rhyme, вЂ‹Mary had a little lamb. вЂ‹And now we're getting some output that looks like that. вЂ‹Actually, what I'm going to do is I'm going to make this a little more specific. вЂ‹My prompt wasn't that great, act as the lamb in the nursery rhyme, вЂ‹Mary had a little lamb. вЂ‹I am going to tell you what Mary is doing, and вЂ‹you will tell me what the lamb is doing. вЂ‹Okay, Mary is in the grocery store. вЂ‹So as the lamb in the nursery rhyme, while Mary is in the grocery store, вЂ‹I would be following her around as closely as possible trying to stay by her side and вЂ‹maybe even nuzzling her hand for attention. вЂ‹Mary is in the movies, As a lamb in the nursery rhyme, вЂ‹while Mary is in the movies, I would not be able to accompany her вЂ‹inside the theater due to my inability to watch movies. вЂ‹So I would probably wait for her outside the theater, вЂ‹perhaps nibbling on some grass or вЂ‹wandering around the nearby area until Mary came back outside, and it goes on. вЂ‹And so you can see that you can create all kinds of interesting вЂ‹personas to produce output for. вЂ‹So we can say, pretend to be this job, вЂ‹pretend to be a speech language pathologist, or вЂ‹pretend to be an accountant, pretend to be a computer scientist. вЂ‹You can make your persona have something to do with the person's point of view or вЂ‹opinion, act as a skeptic so that we can get skeptical output. вЂ‹We can say to act as an inanimate object that may have well known sort of behavior вЂ‹like act as a computer, the Linux terminal for a computer that's been hacked. вЂ‹And we saw that we got all kinds of output that looked like it came from a computer, вЂ‹or we can say act as this character in a nursery rhyme. вЂ‹Tell me what this character is going to do in a particular situation and вЂ‹we're getting that output. вЂ‹So the persona pattern is a way that we can tap into sort of the patterns вЂ‹around language around a specific persona or object or вЂ‹character in a story in order to get output that comes from that point of view, вЂ‹from that role, whatever it is, it's a really, really powerful capability. вЂ‹Now, one of the things is we often see that вЂ‹when large language models are programmed, вЂ‹they actually have a persona that's given to them to guide the whole interaction. вЂ‹So act as a really helpful assistant, and this actually makes a difference. вЂ‹If you tell it to be helpful, it will try to be more helpful. вЂ‹If you tell it to try to do something positive, вЂ‹it's going to try to be more positive. вЂ‹Similarly, if you kind of give it a negative perspective, like my skeptical вЂ‹perspective, it's going to give you output that challenges you or maybe darker. вЂ‹And so, the persona that you ask the large language model to use is really, вЂ‹really important and powerful. вЂ‹The other thing just to note again is it's really information dense. вЂ‹IT has a lot of pattern and knowledge around a persona that if you had to вЂ‹describe it from scratch, you would take up a lot of space in your prompt, вЂ‹you would be losing valuable space in your prompt to provide new information. вЂ‹So if you were providing a lot of new information, you might want to say, вЂ‹act as whatever it is and evaluate this new information. вЂ‹Well, the more space you've taken up in your prompt describing how вЂ‹to do the evaluation and вЂ‹what point of view and other things to take, that's wasting space. вЂ‹But instead if you go and take the persona prop, you say act as this persona, вЂ‹provide outputs that that persona would provide, you're giving it a really, вЂ‹really information dense statement that it can use and вЂ‹allow you to have more space in your prompt for other things. вЂ‹So the persona pattern is a really, really powerful pattern to be aware of and вЂ‹know that it's a very valuable one, you can do all kinds of things, вЂ‹like if you would normally get a committee of people together to discuss вЂ‹different points of view on a particular topic. вЂ‹Well, you can assemble a virtual panel, you can have one prompt, вЂ‹say act as a security expert and analyze my cyber security. вЂ‹You can have another one say act as the Chief Financial Officer, вЂ‹analyze the financial soundness of that same decision. вЂ‹Another one can be act as one of my employees, вЂ‹discuss how this might impact morale. вЂ‹You can provide sort of interesting abilities to get different perspectives, вЂ‹and use those different perspectives to potentially inform decision making or вЂ‹to collect knowledge from different points of view that could be helpful to вЂ‹you in accomplishing a particular task.\"}